race.comment: SQUANDER (7) had just one top-three finish from her first 12 starts but has been in white-hot form of late with two wins and three seconds from his past five. Was beaten 1.5 lengths in town last start, a repeat of which would be good enough here. COSMIC (14) is a late-maturing Japanese mare who has improved each run this prep and looks like she will relish 2000m. OUR PARAMOUR (8) settled well back when 7 lengths from the winner in eighth over 1800m at Sandown-Hillside last start when hard in the market, which was a less impressive effort than her fifth at Seymour the run before. Blinkers off here and draws beautifully to bounce back. MY UNCLE DID IT (12) raced on the speed last start and battled on well but found one better over 2200m at Camperdown. Drawn terribly but has Harry Coffey on.
